Seems like `unsigned long long` is the same size as `uint64_t` on both 32 and 64 bit platforms, making the second condition reduntant (I guess even on master). Would prefer something like the following (so we only potentially fail on unusual/future 128-bit platforms):

```suggestion
    static_assert(sizeof(decltype(bytes)::value_type) == sizeof(decltype(operator""_MiB(mebibytes))));
